OL,6,FThe rail industry produces a
OL,7,Fcancellations score ` counting full
OL,8,Fcancellations as one and part-
OL,9,Fcancellations as half ` which shows
OL,10,Fthe equivalent of 4.0% of the 7.3
OL,11,Fmillion trains planned in that period
OL,12,Fwere cancelled.
OL,14,FThat is the joint worst reliability
OL,15,Fperformance in figures dating back to
OL,16,FMarch 2015, when the annual
OL,17,Fcancellations score was just 1.9%.
